Description: Basic account information, like username, the account creation date, device information, device history (the different devices used to login), an overview of the Terms accepted, and a login history.
Bitmoji Kit lets users easily share their Bitmoji in other apps. When a user links to another app using Bitmoji Kit, Snapchat stores some information about how Bitmoji is used in that app.
Information about Bitmoji
Information provided during Cameos creation flow in Snapchat.
Information about Chats recently sent and received.
Information about Lenses that are created and submitted to Snapchat, including Lens name, the icon of the Lens (if available), and Lens submission date.

Information for when an account is connected to other apps. Snapchat stores information about login history, as well as the information user has chosen to share. Features a list of these apps, whether the user choose to share display name or Bitmoji, time of first connecting Snapchat account, and  login history.
Overview of friends, sent friend requests, as well as blocked or deleted users.
Information about content and users that have reported on Snapchat.
Overview of the surveys responded to on Snap.

Lists the users location history in separate subcategories such as frequent locations, latest location, locations visited, businesses you may have visited in the last two years, areas you may have visited in the last two years. Snapchat uses device’s location to support features like Geofilters, Snap Map, and to show what’s nearby in Search. Snapchat also make guesses about where a user lives and work, so the Bitmoji on Snap Map can reflect what the user might be up to. Even without location permissions, Snapchat can sometimes still guess your approximate location based on your IP address.
Information about the Memories saved in Snapchat.
Information about any purchases made through Snapchat's services such as product purchased and the date of the purchase.

Information used to personalize the services and rank the content seen in Search, Discover, and other places. Ranking contains an overview of content Snapchat thinks the user would be interested in, and some basic information about how the user use their services.

Whenever search is used, the search terms, the approximate location (usually between 200 and 390 square meters), and the current time (within an hour) is stored. After 7 days, Snapchat stores a rougher estimate of the location (usually between 3,200 and 6,240 square meters) for 23 days. Snapchat uses this information to improve search results and our other services.

Information about the Snaps submitted to crowd-sourced services, including Our Story. If the status section says SELECTED, it means that the Snap was selected by the curation team. If the user applied a Geofilter, text, or other creative tools to the content, the submission may contain multiple media files.
Information about commerce activities that have taken place in Snapchat.
Information stored in Snap Ads system.

Overview of the Snap Games the user has played, the number of Friends invited to play, the total number of players in Game, and total time spent using the Voice Party feature. Best scores in select games are stored to show in Leaderboards and share with friends. The user can hide their scores from appearing in friends’ Leaderboards but Snapchat keeps the scores to show the user and help calculate global ranks.
Information about Snaps recently sent and received.

Story history information, which is used to rank Stories content for the user and their friends. Friend and Public Story Views. Includes subsection with overview of Stories that have been watched. A Story can contain multiple Snaps, so Snapchat might show multiple entries per Story. For example, if a Story has 5 Snaps and you only view 3 Snaps, Snapchat show 4 entries below: 3 for the Snap views and 1 for the Story view.
Subscriptions to public users or publications. This package also lists Last Active Timezone.
Information about support inquiries sent to Snapchat Support.
Information about voice and video calls made through Snapchat.
Snap Inc. terms of Service, includes version and Acceptance Date.
Information about user such as app profile, demographics, engagement, discover channels viewed, ads interacted with, interest categories, web and app interactions.
